"title": "8334: reverence, and God's nature",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8334",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Reverence for God results from considering his nature and all that he has done.</p>\n<h2>Believers should revere God and meditate upon his deeds</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:24\">1SA 12:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:14\">JOS 24:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job25:2\">JOB 25:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job37:23-Job37:24\">JOB 37:23–37:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:40-Jer32:41\">JER 32:40–32:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:5\">MAL 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence is to be reserved exclusively for God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:13-Deut6:14\">DEU 6:13–6:14</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's creative activity</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:20-Deut10:21\">DEU 10:20–10:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:18\">1SA 12:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:25\">1CH 16:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:8-Ps33:9\">PSA 33:8–33:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:14\">ECC 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer5:22-Jer5:24\">JER 5:22–5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:2\">HAB 3:2</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's eternal existence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:16\">1TI 6:16</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's name</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:2\">MAL 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:19\">ISA 59:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal1:14\">MAL 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:18\">REV 11:18</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's holiness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:13\">ISA 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:4\">PSA 96:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:23\">ISA 29:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:7\">JER 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:4\">REV 15:4</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's word</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:2\">ISA 66:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:10-Deut4:11\">DEU 4:10–4:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:4\">EZR 9:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:3\">EZR 10:3</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's works</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl3:14\">ECC 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:31\">EXO 14:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:9\">PSA 64:9</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's mercy and compassion</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:7\">PSA 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:23\">PSA 22:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:4\">PSA 130:4</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's intervention in healing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:8\">MAT 9:8</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:12\">MRK 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:26\">LUK 5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's judgment</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:31\">EXO 14:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:8\">AMO 3:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:16\">JON 1:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:7\">REV 14:7</a></p>\n<h2>Reverence for God's anger</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:14-Deut6:15\">DEU 6:14–6:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:11-Ps2:12\">PSA 2:11–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps76:7\">PSA 76:7</a></p>\n<h2>Gentile nations will also revere and fear God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps67:7\">PSA 67:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:24\">JOS 4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:43\">1KI 8:43</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:33\">2CH 6:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:29\">2CH 20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps76:11-Ps76:12\">PSA 76:11–76:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:15\">PSA 102:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:19\">ISA 59:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:9\">JER 33:9</a></p>\n<h2>Reverent fear of God is not mere terror but includes trust</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:20\">EXO 20:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:16-Gen28:17\">GEN 28:16–28:17</a> <em>Jacob feels reverent awe in the presence of the God who has just promised to bless him</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:11\">PSA 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:31\">ACT 9:31</a></p>\n<h2>Reverent fear of God is a remedy against other fears</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:4\">PSA 56:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:4-Luke12:5\">LUK 12:4–12:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:14-1Pet3:15\">1PE 3:14–3:15</a></p>",
